  <identificationInfo>
    <resourceName>Hungarian NER Corpus based on Wikipedia</resourceName>
    <description>
      The text of the corpus will be auto-generated from Hungarian Wikipedia
      articles. It will contain Named Entity (NE) tagging according to the CoNLL
      standard (Person, Organization, Location and Miscellaneous), and
      additional morphological and shallow syntactic annotation. The corpus will
      be the largest ever NE-tagged corpus for Hungarian, which can be used for
      training and testing NE recognizer applications. Thanks to the standard
      tagset, the performance of systems trained on the hunNERwiki corpus will
      be comparable with the performance of other state-of-the-art systems.
      
      Besides the obvious advantages of fully automatic building and annotation
      procedure (reducing the annotation cost), the novelty of the corpus is the
      application of collaboratively constructed resources (Wikipedia, DBpedia).
    </description>
